{
  "texts": [
    "To more precisely locate and fix errors, tools like CubeTesterAI employ an isolation strategy where each generated test method is compiled and executed in a separate file, thereby preventing a single error from compromising the validation process of the entire test suite [54].",
    "Empirical studies consistently indicate that this approach can substantially increase the valid pass rate of generated tests from as low as 24% to over 70% [56,99,161].",
    "This shift fundamentally alters the practical utility of the technology.",
    "Refinement operates at multiple levels.",
    "Beyond simple syntactic fixes, MuTAP [32] performs behavioral repair by feeding back the actual output of the program on failed assertions, enabling the LLM to correct expected values."
  ]
}